    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-10T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-10T05:00:00-05:00" n="498"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.20211/4–1046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-10T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 10, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 10—8:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1119. <gloss target="#t_BBC1">BBC</gloss> this morning reported that <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> has had exchange of correspondence with
                    Soviet Govt concerning Soviet naval officer who was recently arrested by US
                    authorities for espionage. I wish to request that I be completely informed
                    currently of any matter of this sort having to do with activities and treatment
                    of Soviet official personnel in US.<note n="81" xml:id="d498fn81">Telegram 665,
                        April 10, 1946, to Moscow, contained a summary of the developments in this
                        case between April 6 and 9. (861.20211/4–1046)</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> will understand that in instances of this
                    sort Soviet retaliation is always a possibility and we here should be aware in
                    particular of details of any case which may bring counter action against
                    American personnel in USSR.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
